The <Component>CodeBlock</Component> component now supports two additional props to highlight lines: `addedLinesNumbers` and `removedLinesNumbers`.

These can be used to emphasise diffs in code blocks, for example:

<CodeBlock
  filename="next.config.js"
  addedLinesNumbers={[5]}
  removedLinesNumbers={[2, 3, 4]}
  language="jsx"
>
  {`module.exports = {
  experimental: {
    appDir: true,
  },
  appDir: true,
}`}
</CodeBlock>

The <Component>GeistProvider</Component> now uses a forked `@vercel/next-themes` package instead of `next-themes`. This fork enables manual script placement, while the original package automatically inserts the script into the `<body>` tag.
The provider can be used the same way as before. However, the script can be positioned in the `<head>` if you need to. For this, you have to set the new `withScript` prop to `false`. Import <Component>GeistThemeScript</Component> and place it into the `<head>`.

<CodeBlock
  filename="next.config.js"
  addedLinesNumbers={[11, 12, 13, 16]}
  removedLinesNumbers={[15]}
  language="tsx"
>
  {`export default function AppLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: ReactNode;
}): JSX.Element {
  return (
    <html
      // We have to supress hydration because of \`@vercel/next-themes\` within the GeistProvider changes the dom on load
      suppressHydrationWarning
    >
      <head>
        <GeistThemeScript storageKey="zeit-theme" />
      </head>
      <body>
        <GeistProvider storageKey="zeit-theme">
        <GeistProvider storageKey="zeit-theme" withScript={false}>
          {children}
        </GeistProvider>
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}`}
</CodeBlock>

